quran[28]{c,v,t}:
  83,7,"But no, indeed the record{1}of the wicked is in Sijjeen{2}.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘scripture’.|2:Sijjeenis derived from the word ‘sijn’ which means ‘prison’. Here, Allah is expressing the gravity of the matter and describing it as an eternal prison and a painful torment.
  83,8,"And what can make you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>realize what Sijjeen is?"
  83,9,"A written record<a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a>."
  83,10,"Woe on that day to the disbelievers"
  83,11,"who disbelieve in the Day of Recompense,"
  83,12,"for none disbelieves in it except every sinful transgressor"
  83,13,"who, when Our signs{1}are recited to him, says, “Legends of the ancients.”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used isayat(singularayah). Ayahmeans ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Quran,like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose.Each such unit isconsidered a ‘sign’from God.
  83,14,"But no, rather, encrusted over their hearts is what they used to earn."
  83,15,"But no, indeed on that day they are sure to be screened off from their Lord."
  83,16,"Then indeed, they are sure to roast in purgatory."
  83,17,"Then it will be said, “This is what you used to disbelieve in.”"
  83,18,"But no, indeed the record<a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a>of the virtuous is in Elliyyeen{1}.",footnotes:1:Elliyyeen(Elliyyoon) is derived from the word‘uluwwhich means highness.
  83,19,"And what can make you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>realize what Elliyyoon{1}is?",footnotes:1:Elliyyeen(Elliyyoon) is derived from the word‘uluwwhich means highness.
  83,20,"A written record{1},",footnotes:1:Literally ‘scripture’.
  83,21,"witnessed by those brought near."
  83,22,"Indeed, the virtuous are amid bliss,"
  83,23,"on couches, looking on."
  83,24,"<span class=""h"">You</span><a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a><span class=""h"">can recognize<sup foot_note=""81447"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">on their faces the radiance of bliss</span>."
  83,25,"They are given to drink of a sealed nectar,"
  83,26,"<span class=""h"">whose end<sup foot_note=""81448"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">is musk</span>—and this is what competitors should compete for."
  83,27,"And its mixture is of Tasneem,"
  83,28,"a spring from which those brought near drink."
  83,29,"Indeed, those who committed crimes used to laugh at those who had attained faith;"
  83,30,"and when they passed by them, they would wink at one another;"
  83,31,"and when they went back to their families, they would go back jesting;"
  83,32,"and when they saw them, they would say, “These people are most surely misguided.”"
  83,33,"Yet they were not sent as preservers over them."
  83,34,"So today{1}those who have attained faith are laughing at the deniers,",footnotes:1:Referring to the Day of Judgment.
